{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/cataracts/background-information/prevalence/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"79a1f298-b9fa-5e11-bf8c-e4c5b4994859","slug":"prevalence","fullItemName":"Prevalence","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field fa660411-501e-427b-823d-31d7a5aaa7d5 --><h2>How common is it?</h2><!-- end field fa660411-501e-427b-823d-31d7a5aaa7d5 -->","summary":"","htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 035c9147-2c2e-457b-9d44-bd8727b7e3d5 --><!-- begin field 068e1ccb-380b-45d2-8daa-ea4c7f042063 --><ul><li>Around 36 million people worldwide are blind, and in over 12 million of them this is due to cataract [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cataracts/references/\">Hashemi, 2020</a>].   </li><li>A systematic review and meta-analysis of the regional and global prevalence of age-related cataracts found that the age-standardised pooled prevalence estimate (ASPPE) of any cataract was 17.2% and the pooled prevalence estimate (PPE) of any cataract in people aged [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cataracts/references/\">Hashemi, 2020</a>]:  <ul><li>20–39 years was 3.01%.</li><li>40–59 years was 16.97%.</li><li>Over 60 years was 54.38%.</li></ul></li><li>These values were, respectively [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cataracts/references/\">Hashemi, 2020</a>]:  <ul><li>2.18%, 7.26%, and 24.78% for cortical cataract. </li><li>1.12%, 5.77%, and 31.19% for nuclear cataract. </li><li>0.52%, 1.91%, and 7.29% for posterior subcapsular cataract.</li></ul></li><li>A UK study that randomly sampled 1547 people 65 years of age and older found that the prevalence of visually-impairing cataracts was [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cataracts/references/\">Reidy et al, 1998</a>]: <ul><li>71% in people aged over 85 years. </li><li>59% in people aged 80–84 years.</li><li>42% in people aged 75–79 years.</li><li>24% in people aged 70–74 years.</li><li>16% in people aged 65–69 years.</li></ul></li><li>Cataract surgery is the most common elective surgical procedure in the UK [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cataracts/references/\">RCO, 2018</a>]. </li><li>Cataracts in children are much less common. An observational study in the UK found that [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cataracts/references/\">Rahi et al, 2001</a>]: <ul><li>About 3 in 10,000 children were diagnosed with cataract by the age of 1 year (two-thirds had bilateral cataracts, one-third had a unilateral cataract).</li><li>This increased to 4 in 10,000 children by 15 years of age.</li></ul></li></ul><!-- end field 068e1ccb-380b-45d2-8daa-ea4c7f042063 --><!-- end item 035c9147-2c2e-457b-9d44-bd8727b7e3d5 -->","topic":{"id":"eeb34712-def5-5b38-9125-fec8925c1bcc","topicId":"9a3fe0f5-1b06-4ff6-9a79-2ed4a8f4b2c5","topicName":"Cataracts","slug":"cataracts","lastRevised":"Last revised in March 2020","chapters":[{"id":"90f4d5e6-8dee-54a2-b535-a3280c9ff7e9","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"da1f4019-d02d-523b-80ce-e4ba8579b43d","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"87a3b79a-dbff-50b1-a10c-fc54f60080f3","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"cd79c0cf-e5a8-5fb6-99af-3d9e0eaf4b28","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"d0c360ad-3631-54ab-809e-570769cd5aa1","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"8af6938b-ae1b-5c2a-8b8c-826edbed8669","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"9ed0ddb2-07a6-5c9e-86b8-740894cd88e7","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"d3db836f-68b9-5c32-bb04-1d6c9b755015","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"7